Harris. They made the Times, which didn't duck at least that duty, seem downright brave by comparison.</description><guid isPermaLink="false">113376378406789808</guid><pubDate>Sat, 26 Oct 2024 23:44:02 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Boris Barbour</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@BorisBarbour/113378973490067302</link><description>MDPI have lost their way. Or more likely never found it in the first place. h/t &lt;span class="h-card" translate="no"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://mastodon.social/@deevybee"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;deevybee&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; I think we must conclude that paying for publication creates perverse incentives that are irresistible.But some form of the problem will remain for as long as people count publications rather than examine content. A fake paper costs 1/100th (?) of the research to produce a real one. Current incentives against low-quality production do not balance that massive factor.&lt;a href="https://pubpeer.com/publications/77E4AB0FFADF8913053B6CE8D61085#9" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" translate="no"&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;https://&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="ellipsis"&gt;pubpeer.com/publications/77E4A&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="invisible"&gt;B0FFADF8913053B6CE8D61085#9&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">113378973490067302</guid><pubDate>Sun, 27 Oct 2024 10:44:00 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Boris Barbour</title><link>https://mastodon.social/@BorisBarbour/113378977336855846</link><description>&lt;span class="h-card" translate="no"&gt;&lt;a class="u-url mention" href="https://mastodon.social/@deevybee"&gt;@&lt;span&gt;deevybee&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; Until publishing crap becomes a strong career negative, we are lost.</description><guid isPermaLink="false">113378977336855846</guid><pubDate>Sun, 27 Oct 2024 10:44:59 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Noah Cook</title><link>https://med-mastodon.com/@UncivilServant/11337434593